        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1978-02-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1978-02-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="213"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d213">
                <head>213. Note From President <persName corresp="#p_CJE_1">Carter</persName> to the
                    President’s Assistant for National Security Affairs (<persName corresp="#p_BZ_1"
                        >Brzezinski</persName>)<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d213fn1">Source:
                        Carter Library, President’s Plains File, President’s Personal Foreign
                        Affairs File, Box 2, 11/77–2/79. No classification marking. <persName
                            corresp="#p_CJE_1">Carter</persName> wrote the note by hand.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1978-02-07">February 7, 1978</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <salute>To Zbig</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I have examined all my notes &amp; dictation from the 12/16 &amp; 12/17 meetings
                    with <persName corresp="#p_BM_2">Begin</persName>.<note n="2" xml:id="d213fn2"
                        >No notes or dictation have been found. For the memoranda of conversation of
                        the December 16 and 17 meetings with <persName corresp="#p_BM_2"
                            >Begin</persName>, see <ref target="#d177">Documents 177</ref> and <ref
                            target="#d178">178</ref>. In his meeting with <persName
                            corresp="#p_VC_1">Vance</persName> on January 16, <persName
                            corresp="#p_BM_2">Begin</persName> expressed his contention that he had
                        left the White House “with so many blessings” after his December 16 and 17
                        meetings with President <persName corresp="#p_CJE_1">Carter</persName>,
                        where he discussed his plan to keep Israeli settlements in the Sinai. See
                            <ref target="#d195">Document 195</ref>.</note> During my <hi
                        rend="italic">private</hi> meeting he discussed a) IL 76’s→Iraq, b) The need
                    to expedite a decision on weapon sales to Israel, &amp; c) his hope that we
                    would give support to Ethiopia against Somalia. Never any discussion of
                    settlements.</p>
                <p>In the general meeting he now says he talked of settlements in Sinai—I don’t
                    recall it &amp; it isn’t in my current (then) notes. No one in U.S. gov’t to my
                    knowledge has ever accepted the need, propriety or legality of Israeli civilian
                    settlements on occupied territory. In referring to his general Sinai proposal I
                    said then that it sounded reasonable.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="strong">J.C.</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
